      • getGapCount

        public int getGapCount()
        Non-projectivity: gives the number of "gaps" in the node's yield. Each gap is defined as a series of one or more tokens which are not members of the node's yield, but which are contained between two tokens which are members of the node's yield.

      • getGapDegree

        public <any> getGapDegree()
        Non-projectivity: returns the node with the maximum gap count in this sub-tree.

      • getEdgeCount

        public int getEdgeCount()
        Non-projectivity: for each edge directly governed by this node, counts the number of connected components contained inside the interval defined by the edge, which are not themselves dominated by this node, i.e. not contained in the node's yield. A connected component is a connected subtree. Returns the maximum edge count.

      • getEdgeDegree

        public <any> getEdgeDegree()
        Non-projectivity: returns the node with the maximum edge count in this sub-tree.
